    <text id="B2059T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Manly writes that he needs more details about a prospective teacher in New Hope,
                    in Augusta County, before he can pay her.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Henry Morris<lb/>New Hope, Augusta <abbr expan="County"
                            >Co.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1870-01-09"><abbr expan="January">Jan</abbr> 9 <abbr
                                expan="1870">70</abbr></date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You did not give the name of the person who proposes to teach, nor state whether
                    she is colored or white, and I have no means of judging of her qualifications.
                    If I am to pay a teacher, I ought to know about these matters. The price I could
                    pay must depend also upon the size of the school. The teacher had better
                    commence her school at once and then write a letter with her own hand, telling
                    me how many pupils she has &amp;c.</p>

                <p>I pay monthly.</p>

                <p>Please state in your reply the exact location of the school, and how it can be
                    reached from the Chesapeake &amp; Ohio <abbr expan="Railroad">RR</abbr>.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Truly</salute>
                    <signed>R. M. Manly<lb/><abbr expan="Superintendent">Supt Ed.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
